      • Post

        public Post(org.json.JSONObject json)
     throws org.json.JSONException
        Creates a bare (uninstantiated) Post from a JSON that conforms to the below format: 
         
 {
         "id": 0,
         "id_user": 0,
         "id_network": 0,
         "post_date": "string",
         "post_text": "string",
         "post_class": 0,
         "post_original": "string",
         "vid_link": "string",
         "img_link": "string"
        }
        Parameters:
        json - JSON representation of the Post to construct
        Throws:
        org.json.JSONException - May be thrown in response to an improperly formatted JSON

      • toJSON

        public org.json.JSONObject toJSON()
                           throws org.json.JSONException
        Generate a JSON describing the object. The JSON will conform to the following format: 
             
          {
                    "id_user": 0,
                    "id_network": 0,
                    "post_text": "string",
                    "vid_link": "string",
                    "img_link": "string"
                }
        The resulting object is suitable for use with the /post/new endpoint.
        Returns:
        JSON representation of the object
        Throws:
        org.json.JSONException - Unclear when this would be thrown
